  • Reference

    Linear Regression

    our_lm.Rd

    Estimates a vector for the model coefficients. It also computes model evaluation metrics.

    Usage,
    our_lm(y, X, alpha = 0.05)

    Arguments

    y

    A vector of length n that represents the response variable of interest that we would like to explain/predict.

    X

    A matrix of dimension n x p that represents the independent (explanatory) variables.

    alpha

    A numeric (double) used to denote the significance level.

    Value

    A list containing the following attributes:

    beta

    Estimated coefficient vector

    sigma2

    Estimated variance

    variance_beta

    Estimated variance for each beta

    r_squared

    Coefficient of determination

    mallow

    Mallow's C_p

    f_stat

    F-statistic

    p_value

    Determined by F-statistic

    ci

    Interval of values based on alpha

    res

    Model Residuals

    preds

    Model Predictions

    Author

    Clayton Haley

    Ukamaka Victoria Nnyaba

    Robert Fett

    Examples

    x <- matrix(rnorm(400), ncol = 4) # so this is a 100x4 predictor matrix
y <- rnorm(100)
model <- our_lm(y, x, alpha = 0.05)
